Here are sources for Census data (to analyze neighborhood changes over time):

* [American Fact Finder](https://factfinder.census.gov/), the official source for US Census data, including ACS data.
* You can also use [Social Explorer](https://www.socialexplorer.com/explore-maps) to generate maps using US Census data, including ACS data 
* The NYC Census FactFinder is a valuable resource for determining neighborhood boundaries
* Here is an [example] of how to set up a table in Excel in order to visualize trends related to neighborhood change over time (using data downloaded from Social Explorer).
